Package: faSTM
Title: Fast Structural Topic Models
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Neal", "Caren", email = "neal.caren@unc.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A fast, modern implementation of the Structural Topic Model. faSTM
    fits the logistic-normal STM (with prevalence and content covariates) via a
    Rust core, in seconds where the original 'stm' package takes minutes, and
    scales to large corpora through an opt-in stochastic-variational path. It is
    self-contained: text preparation is read from 'quanteda' or 'tidytext'
    objects, model inspection (labelTopics with FREX/lift/score, findThoughts,
    semantic coherence, exclusivity, topic correlations) and an honest
    estimateEffect() (method-of-composition posterior propagation) are built in.
    The fitted object is structurally compatible with 'stm' so existing analyses
    migrate with minimal changes.
